  "prompt": "What are 13.1 and 26.2 stickers and what do they mean?",
  "response": "The stickers \"13.1\" and \"26.2\" refer to the distances of half marathons and marathons, respectively. \n\n- **13.1 sticker**: This signifies that the individual has completed a half marathon, which is 13.1 miles (21.1 kilometers) long.\n  \n- **26.2 sticker**: This indicates that the individual has finished a full marathon, which is 26.2 miles (42.2 kilometers) long.\n\nThese stickers are commonly seen on the backs of cars, water bottles, or other personal items as a way for runners to celebrate their achievements and show pride in their endurance running accomplishments.",
